573
00:34:23,680 --> 00:34:26,162
so that it's as good as it can be for every playthrough

574
00:34:26,202 --> 00:34:27,643
that we can generate and we can make.

575
00:34:28,243 --> 00:34:29,464
We tune it, essentially.

576
00:34:30,305 --> 00:34:31,846
So into this top-down process,

577
00:34:32,166 --> 00:34:32,286
we...

578
00:34:33,543 --> 00:34:37,145
basically get the characters to talk one topic at a time.

579
00:34:37,746 --> 00:34:40,127
Topics are introduced in priority order.

580
00:34:40,467 --> 00:34:42,128
They are whatever we say they are.

581
00:34:42,168 --> 00:34:43,669
A topic has no formal definition.

582
00:34:43,810 --> 00:34:46,651
So it could be a broad concept like Malcolm's gone missing,

583
00:34:46,932 --> 00:34:47,692
your husband's gone missing,

584
00:34:48,152 --> 00:34:49,453
or it could be a specific detail

585
00:34:49,613 --> 00:34:51,314
like Veronica's earring was found

586
00:34:51,354 --> 00:34:52,655
on the upper deck at the crime scene.

587
00:34:53,699 --> 00:34:56,501
We deal with really important topics first.

588
00:34:57,382 --> 00:35:00,645
Things like, somebody saw you killing someone.

589
00:35:00,705 --> 00:35:02,086
Well, okay, that's a straight game over.

590
00:35:02,326 --> 00:35:04,248
We want as little redundancy as possible

591
00:35:04,308 --> 00:35:04,929
in each playthrough.

592
00:35:04,969 --> 00:35:07,731
We don't want people going through an enormous scene

